 of Narwhal, the lightweight pub/sub server i shared a while ago. the biggest change in v0.5.0 is the migration from tokio to monoio as the primary async runtime, which means the server now runs entirely on io_uring on Linux:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/narwhal-io/narwhal/releases/tag/narwhal-0.5.0\r\n\r\nthe project is still alpha, but the core is getting more solid with each release. would love feedback, especially from anyone who has experience tuning io_uring-based servers. i'm sure there's still a lot of room to squeeze more out of it. :)","submitter_user":"ortuman","user_is_author":true,"tags":["distributed","linux","performance","programming","rust"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/fztjyg","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/fztjyg/narwhal_v0_5_0_pub_sub_messaging_server_now"},{"short_id":"bp15oz","created_at":"2026-03-02T05:44:12.000-06:00","title":"Kovan: From Production MVCC Systems to Wait-Free Memory Reclamation","url":"https://vertexclique.com/blog/kovan-from-prod-to-mr/","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"sp6370","user_is_author":false,"tags":["formalmethods","rust"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/bp15oz","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/bp15oz/kovan_from_production_mvcc_systems_wait"},{"short_id":"rlof2z","created_at":"2026-03-02T05:21:20.000-06:00","title":"libxml2 Enterprise Edition (AGPL, from the previous maintainer)","url":"https://codeberg.org/nwellnhof/libxml2-ee","score":7,"flags":0,"comment_count":5,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"gioele","user_is_author":false,"tags":["programming"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rlof2z","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rlof2z/libxml2_enterprise_edition_agpl_from"},{"short_id":"uqpww1","created_at":"2026-03-02T04:46:59.000-06:00","title":"Building a Quake PC","url":"https://fabiensanglard.net/quake_pc/","score":6,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"luke808